02:55.449 --> 02:57.083
Jack: Pass.

02:57.085 --> 02:59.319
Unh-unh.

02:59.321 --> 03:01.020
[ keyboard clacking ]
Kid in a costume.

03:01.022 --> 03:03.056
Balloon.

03:03.058 --> 03:04.357
Nope.

03:04.359 --> 03:06.993
Uh, hold.

03:06.995 --> 03:08.428
The camera sure loves Bee.

03:08.430 --> 03:09.829
What can you do?

03:09.831 --> 03:12.332
When you're a superstar,
you're paparazzi bait.

03:12.334 --> 03:14.334
Wait.
Is that Bumblebee?

03:14.336 --> 03:15.735
On a conspiracy website

03:15.737 --> 03:18.371
where users post evidence
of close encounters.

03:18.373 --> 03:20.673
But we have it
under control, Ratchet.

03:20.675 --> 03:23.609
We just scrub
and replace Bee with...

03:23.611 --> 03:26.713
<i>Mars cat says,
"take me to your feeder."</i>

03:26.715 --> 03:28.848
[ laughs ]

03:28.850 --> 03:32.051
Ratchet actually laughed?

03:32.053 --> 03:33.753
Uh...

03:33.755 --> 03:34.887
[ chuckles ]

03:34.889 --> 03:37.357
Um, Optimus, do you want
to see something funny?

03:37.359 --> 03:38.691
No.

03:38.693 --> 03:40.326
Arcee:
Don't take it personally.

03:40.328 --> 03:41.961
Primes are built that way.

03:41.963 --> 03:45.064
Never seen Optimus laugh,
cry, or lose his cool.

03:45.066 --> 03:47.667
While Optimus certainly
keeps his emotions in check,

03:47.669 --> 03:51.037
I've known him far longer
than any of you have,

03:51.039 --> 03:54.474
and he was different
before he was made a Prime.

03:54.476 --> 03:56.909
Optimus wasn't always a Prime?

03:56.911 --> 03:59.612
On Cybertron,
one isn't born into greatness.

03:59.614 --> 04:01.647
Rather, one must earn it.

04:01.649 --> 04:05.518
So, different how?
We talkin' party animal?

04:05.520 --> 04:06.519
No, no.

04:06.521 --> 04:08.388
Optimus was more like...

04:09.923 --> 04:10.957
...Jack.

04:10.959 --> 04:12.658
What?
I'm nothing like Opt--

04:12.660 --> 04:13.960
<i>Fowler: Prime!</i>

04:13.962 --> 04:16.396
<i>Those techites my department's
been tracking --</i>

04:16.398 --> 04:17.529
<i>We figured it was MECH</i>

04:17.531 --> 04:19.399
<i>on account of the stealth tactics</i>

04:19.401 --> 04:21.466
<i>until moments ago
when a security feed</i>

04:21.469 --> 04:23.603
<i>at the Pennington ebbs
particle collider</i>

04:23.605 --> 04:25.772
<i>captured this.</i>

04:25.774 --> 04:27.640
[ beep ]
Soundwave.

04:27.642 --> 04:29.976
Raf can swap that out for you
with a funny cap.

04:29.978 --> 04:31.344
<i>The 'Con without a face</i>

04:31.346 --> 04:33.946
<i>made off with
a cutting-edge phase conductor.</i>

04:33.948 --> 04:35.314
<i>Here's a punch list</i>

04:35.316 --> 04:37.583
<i>of everything else
we've confirmed stolen to date.</i>

04:37.585 --> 04:38.751
[ beep ]

04:38.753 --> 04:42.755
Plasma injector,
neutron shield, tesserat?

04:42.757 --> 04:44.490
There's only one thing missing

04:44.492 --> 04:46.325
if they are intending to build...

04:46.327 --> 04:49.028
Knockout: The decepticon
space bridge 2.0

04:49.030 --> 04:51.097
is nearly ready to launch.

04:51.099 --> 04:52.965
All we require is...

04:52.967 --> 04:55.902
[ beeping ]

04:55.904 --> 04:59.505
what Soundwave said --
an ample power source.

04:59.507 --> 05:03.509
Airachnid: This one lies within
a highly fortified location,

05:03.511 --> 05:06.813
by human standards.
I could tunnel in.

05:06.815 --> 05:09.715
The time of prophecy
is nearly upon us!

05:13.020 --> 05:16.155
We can no longer afford stealth.

05:18.192 --> 05:21.561
<i>Prime, the 'Cons really
stepped in it this time.</i>

05:21.563 --> 05:23.196
<i>They hit a U.S. military lab.</i>

05:23.198 --> 05:25.398
<i>Our boys in green
will fend them off</i>

05:25.400 --> 05:26.666
<i>till your team shows.</i>

05:26.668 --> 05:29.702
Agent Fowler, I fear
that Megatron's desperation

05:29.704 --> 05:31.504
may be at its zenith,

05:31.506 --> 05:33.973
and you know
that I cannot condone

05:33.975 --> 05:36.809
even a single human casualty.

05:36.811 --> 05:39.045
[ sighs ] Fowler here.

05:39.047 --> 05:42.281
Evacuate all personnel,
immediately.

05:45.252 --> 05:47.253
[ gunfire ]

05:49.323 --> 05:50.289
Retreat!

06:24.458 --> 06:28.961
<i>Breakdown: Lord Megatron, package secured,
but the Autobots have arrived.</i>

06:28.963 --> 06:30.363
Ah!

06:30.365 --> 06:32.965
Prepare the warship
for rendezvous.

06:32.967 --> 06:35.701
The package will be ready
for pickup!

06:39.973 --> 06:42.675
<i>Ratchet: Bumblebee,
the team may require backup.</i>

06:42.677 --> 06:45.678
<i>They are three clicks north
from your current position,</i>

06:45.680 --> 06:46.913
<i>just off the highway.</i>

06:46.915 --> 06:48.814
<i>If you drop Raf at the exit ramp,</i>

06:48.816 --> 06:51.083
<i>I can bridge him back to base
from there.</i>

06:51.085 --> 06:53.119
[ buzzing ]

06:53.121 --> 06:54.153
It's okay, Bee.

06:54.155 --> 06:56.188
We'll go racing another time.

07:04.298 --> 07:06.666
Well, well.

07:06.668 --> 07:10.002
A foolish scout
has strayed from the ranks.

07:21.448 --> 07:23.549
[ buzzing ]

07:33.180 --> 07:34.180
Ugh!

07:56.137 --> 07:58.071
Optimus.

07:58.073 --> 08:00.673
Megatron,
do you not see the folly

08:00.675 --> 08:03.743
in trying to force
a prophecy to fruition?

08:03.745 --> 08:06.212
Why leave matters to fate

08:06.214 --> 08:09.382
if one can forge
one's own destiny?

08:09.384 --> 08:12.318
Ah, speaking of fate...

08:23.597 --> 08:24.731
Raf!

08:25.866 --> 08:28.768
He's breathing...
Barely.

08:28.770 --> 08:30.503
Ah-ha.

08:30.505 --> 08:35.008
It would seem I swatted a Bee
and squashed a bug.

08:35.010 --> 08:37.110
[ buzzing ]

08:37.111 --> 08:39.212
Bee, no!

08:40.815 --> 08:42.182
[ chuckles ]

08:42.183 --> 08:45.952
Ratchet, bridge us back now.

08:45.954 --> 08:48.822
We must have an Autobot down.

08:55.996 --> 09:00.700
Arcee, attend to Rafael
and Bumblebee.

09:35.503 --> 09:36.536
Raf?

09:36.538 --> 09:37.504
No!

09:37.506 --> 09:38.771
What happened?

09:38.773 --> 09:40.106
Megatron.

09:40.108 --> 09:42.275
Quickly, into my laboratory.

09:54.722 --> 09:56.723
[ monitor beeps ]

09:59.793 --> 10:01.561
Rafael isn't responding.

10:01.563 --> 10:04.831
We must run diagnostics
of his assemblage --

10:04.833 --> 10:06.399
eh, vital statistics.

10:06.401 --> 10:09.035
Oh, my tools --
they're all wrong!

10:09.037 --> 10:10.436
[ glass shatters ]
[ buzzing ]

10:10.438 --> 10:12.906
We need to call my mom.

10:12.908 --> 10:14.374
Your mother may be a nurse,

10:14.376 --> 10:16.276
but does she know anything
about the effects of Energon

10:16.278 --> 10:17.877
on the human body?

10:17.879 --> 10:20.346
Wh-- do you know anything
about the human body?

10:21.949 --> 10:25.185
Mom, it's urgent!

10:25.187 --> 10:28.421
"The weak will perish."

10:28.423 --> 10:31.958
Be strong, Rafael.

10:36.964 --> 10:39.832
Knockout: The power source
will be rigged in no time,

10:39.834 --> 10:40.867
Lord Megatron.

10:40.869 --> 10:43.469
We're nearly
at the construction site.

10:43.471 --> 10:45.238
"Nearly" isn't good enough.

10:45.240 --> 10:46.773
The spheres are aligning.

10:46.775 --> 10:48.808
I must not miss
my moment to --

10:48.810 --> 10:49.976
[ coughs, gasps ]

10:56.483 --> 10:58.551
Lord Megatron,
are you all right?

10:58.553 --> 11:02.589
Yet again, it is as if
I can hear Unicron's thoughts.

11:02.591 --> 11:05.124
Unicron, the chaos bringer?

11:05.126 --> 11:08.261
They say Dark Energon
is his blood.

11:08.263 --> 11:09.596
Heh, whatever.

11:09.598 --> 11:11.998
Complete the space bridge.

11:12.000 --> 11:15.501
There is something
I must attend to.

11:18.572 --> 11:21.574
Does he seem to be losing it?

11:21.576 --> 11:23.710
A bit.

11:27.781 --> 11:29.182
Mom, thank --

11:29.184 --> 11:30.516
Grab my bag!

11:30.518 --> 11:31.684
[ monitor beeping ]

11:34.788 --> 11:36.656
Measuring the extent
of the absorption

11:36.658 --> 11:38.891
should determine
the proper course of treatment.

11:38.893 --> 11:40.793
If I don't get this boy
stabilized now,

11:40.795 --> 11:42.295
he will not leave
this table alive.

11:42.297 --> 11:43.296
Do you understand me?

11:43.298 --> 11:44.497
Uh...

11:48.535 --> 11:50.770
[ buzzing ]

11:52.006 --> 11:53.706
Bee, listen.

11:53.708 --> 11:55.708
You think I don't know
how it feels

11:55.710 --> 11:57.443
to watch a partner...
Harmed?

11:57.445 --> 11:59.345
Revenge won't help Raf
right now.

11:59.347 --> 12:01.581
You need to keep
your emotions in check.

12:06.453 --> 12:07.787
[ buzzes ]

12:13.694 --> 12:14.727
[ clanging ]

12:28.575 --> 12:31.077
Ratchet, how is Rafael?

12:31.079 --> 12:33.579
It is too soon to know.

12:33.581 --> 12:35.748
He's in good hands.

12:35.750 --> 12:37.917
Not mine, Optimus.

12:37.919 --> 12:40.353
Curse my cybertronian pride.

12:40.355 --> 12:42.488
We've accepted these humans
into our lives,

12:42.490 --> 12:44.223
yet I bothered to learn
so little

12:44.225 --> 12:47.160
of their science or medicine.

12:47.162 --> 12:49.429
Pull yourself together,
old friend.

12:49.431 --> 12:50.997
Rafael needs you.

12:50.999 --> 12:54.033
And I have grown to need him.

12:54.035 --> 12:58.271
Lock on to my coordinates
and activate the ground bridge.

12:58.273 --> 12:59.872
[ grunts ]

12:59.874 --> 13:01.074
Ready.

13:02.242 --> 13:04.510
Bulkhead, return to base.

13:04.512 --> 13:06.946
There is something
I must do.

13:06.948 --> 13:08.748
R-- serious?

13:08.750 --> 13:10.583
I have been foolish not to see

13:10.585 --> 13:14.620
what history has proven
over and over again --

13:14.622 --> 13:18.725
that Autobots and Decepticons
will never mend their ways.

13:18.727 --> 13:21.794
If there can be
no diplomatic solution

13:21.796 --> 13:23.896
to this perpetual conflict,

13:23.898 --> 13:27.300
then I must not allow
more darkness to fall

13:27.302 --> 13:31.104
upon this or any planet.

13:31.106 --> 13:35.341
Megatron must be destroyed.

13:48.224 --> 13:52.694
I have come for Megatron,
and him alone.

13:52.696 --> 13:55.163
Stand down and be spared.

14:09.078 --> 14:11.980
Megatron: The flaming mountain
in my visions...

14:13.949 --> 14:17.585
...as if it summoned me here,
guided me.

14:17.587 --> 14:21.556
This is where I am
to position my space bridge --

14:21.558 --> 14:26.327
the place from whence
I am to harvest Dark Energon!

14:26.329 --> 14:27.762
Optimus: Megatron!

14:27.764 --> 14:30.031
I am here on your ship.

14:30.033 --> 14:31.966
Come and face me.

14:33.903 --> 14:36.771
The place in which 
I am to defeat

14:36.773 --> 14:39.174
the last of the Primes.

14:39.176 --> 14:40.441
Hear this!

14:40.443 --> 14:44.078
<i>Any Decepticon who lays
a hand on Optimus Prime</i>

14:44.080 --> 14:46.314
<i>will answer to me.</i>

14:46.316 --> 14:49.083
<i>Soundwave,
lock on to my coordinates</i>

14:49.085 --> 14:54.722
<i>and lead my opponent
to his destiny!</i>

14:57.960 --> 15:00.461
[ beeping ]

15:00.463 --> 15:02.230
Jack, help me get Raf
to the car.

15:02.232 --> 15:04.032
He's going to the 
emergency room.

15:04.034 --> 15:07.068
Nurse Darby, your doctors
won't be able to comprehend

15:07.070 --> 15:10.772
what's afflicting him --
not without a decade of study.

15:10.774 --> 15:12.774
I don't have time to argue.

15:12.776 --> 15:15.310
The effects of an energon blast
on an autobot

15:15.312 --> 15:18.813
can be devastating enough,
but this is a human.

15:18.815 --> 15:20.882
I'm not getting any readings.

15:20.884 --> 15:22.784
How could I not have seen this?

15:22.786 --> 15:27.288
Rafael's been infected
with Dark Energon.

15:35.898 --> 15:39.701
Megatron, today you answer
for your crimes

15:39.703 --> 15:43.871
against Cybertron
and against humanity.

15:43.873 --> 15:45.873
One shall stand...

15:45.875 --> 15:48.276
And one shall fall --

15:48.278 --> 15:51.179
You, Optimus Prime!

15:51.181 --> 15:53.214
[ both grunting ]

15:56.385 --> 15:59.821
If Dark Energon is devouring
Raf from the inside out,

15:59.823 --> 16:04.459
we must expel it and fast,
the only possible way I know.

16:04.461 --> 16:06.261
I need Energon.

16:06.263 --> 16:07.362
Wait.

16:07.364 --> 16:10.298
You said Energon
was devastating to humans.

16:10.300 --> 16:12.333
Under normal circumstances,
quite.

16:12.335 --> 16:14.502
But I am relying upon
the dark matter

16:14.504 --> 16:18.339
currently invading Rafael's body
to meet it head on.

16:29.118 --> 16:30.118
Yah!

16:49.738 --> 16:52.974
Your defeat here was 
foreseen by the ancients.

16:52.976 --> 16:56.311
What was it they wrote --
"the weak shall perish"?

16:56.313 --> 16:59.347
Do not believe
everything you read.

17:04.420 --> 17:06.421
[ rapid beeping ]

17:09.391 --> 17:12.960
I need him over here now!

17:15.464 --> 17:17.498
[ steady beeping ]

17:19.734 --> 17:22.670
[ whirring ]

17:33.649 --> 17:35.616
[ beeping ]

17:49.698 --> 17:52.934
Raf: [ sighs ]
Pulse rate is stabilizing.

17:52.936 --> 17:55.069
[ weakly ] bee.

17:55.071 --> 17:56.604
[ buzzes ]

17:56.606 --> 17:58.039
Ah.

18:03.212 --> 18:05.980
Optimus, we did it.

18:05.982 --> 18:07.348
[ roars ]

18:14.323 --> 18:15.490
Aah!

18:24.133 --> 18:25.700
Aah!

18:27.269 --> 18:29.937
Yahh!

18:29.939 --> 18:31.406
[ tires screeching ]

18:54.096 --> 18:55.530
Yah!

18:59.134 --> 19:01.469
[ panting ]

19:06.608 --> 19:09.310
My destiny!

19:10.312 --> 19:13.548
This isn't how it's 
supposed to end!

19:13.550 --> 19:17.919
On the contrary, Megatron.

19:20.322 --> 19:24.258
I could not have allowed
this to end otherwise.

19:41.343 --> 19:44.011
Bulkhead, you let Optimus
face Megatron alone?

19:44.013 --> 19:45.646
I didn't have a choice.

19:45.648 --> 19:47.081
It could be a trap.

19:47.083 --> 19:49.150
We need to get a fix
on his location.

19:51.186 --> 19:53.254
[ growls ]

19:57.693 --> 20:00.194
How was it that you put it,
Optimus?

20:00.196 --> 20:03.431
"I could not have allowed
this to end otherwise"?

20:16.411 --> 20:18.746
Aaaaah!

20:35.097 --> 20:37.398
[ grunts ]

20:41.069 --> 20:43.070
I'm locked onto
Optimus' signal.

20:43.072 --> 20:44.839
Wait.

20:44.841 --> 20:46.574
How is this possible?

20:46.576 --> 20:48.042
What? What is it?

20:48.044 --> 20:52.179
We need to get Optimus
out of there now!

20:57.886 --> 21:00.821
[ laughs ]

21:00.823 --> 21:02.857
Well, well.

21:02.859 --> 21:06.460
It seem the blood
of Unicron I've been seeking

21:06.462 --> 21:11.399
is not out there,
but rather... right here.

21:11.401 --> 21:15.336
Dark Energon erupting
from the earth...?

